'''Badobre Emmanuel Elysee Djedje Agbadou''' (born 17 June 1997) is an Ivorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]] and the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].<ref name="SW">{{Soccerway|emmanuel-agbadou/622534}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Beşiktaşımıza Hoş Geldin Badobre Emmanuel Elysee Djedje Agbadou |url=https://bjk.com.tr/tr/haber/93573 |date=6 February 2026 |access-date=6 February 2026 |publisher=Beşiktaş J.K. |language=tr}}</ref>

==Club career==

===Monastir===
In July 2019, Agbadou signed for [[US Monastir (football)|US Monastir]]. On 25 September 2019, he played his first match against [[Stade Tunisien]] in a 1–0 win.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/25/tunisia/ligue-1/us-monastirienne/stade-tunisien/3120785|title=Monastir vs. Stade Tunisien – 25 September 2019|date=25 September 2019|accessdate=2 October 2019}}</ref>

===Eupen===
On 1 September 2020, Agbadou join Belgian club [[K.A.S. Eupen|Eupen]].<ref>{{cite web|date=7 July 2019 |title=Mercato: Agbadou Emmanuel (FC San Pedro) rejoint la Tunisie |url=https://mondialsport.ci/mercato-agbadou-emmanuel-fc-san-pedro-rejoint-la-tunisie-6742.sport |website=mondialsport.ci}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> He played his first professional match on 30 October 2020, in a championship match against the [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]], which ended with a 4–0 defeat for his team.

===Reims===
On 16 June 2022, Agbadou signed a five-year contract with [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] in France.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Reims|url=https://www.stade-de-reims.com/emmanuel-agbadou-colosse-aux-pieds-agiles/|title=Emmanuel Agbadou, colosse aux pieds agiles|date=16 June 2022|access-date=7 July 2022|language=fr}}</ref>

Agbadou plays his first game under his on 7 August 2022, in the first day of the 2022–23 season of [[Ligue 1]], against the [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]].

On 20 September 2024, Agbadou extended his contract with the Reims by one more season, that is, until June 2028.<ref>{{cite web|date=20 September 2024 |title=Emmanuel Agbadou (Reims) prolonge son contrat d'un an, jusqu'en 2028 |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Emmanuel-agbadou-reims-prolonge-son-contrat-d-un-an-jusqu-en-2028/1508861 |website=L'Équipe}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

===Wolverhampton Wanderers===
On 9 January 2025, Agbadou signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] on a four-and-a-half-year deal for a reported fee of £16.6&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cx2p053nplgo|title=Wolves sign Reims defender Agbadou for £16.6m|work=BBC Sport|date=9 January 2025|accessdate=9 January 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20250109-wolves-complete-agbadou-signing/|title=Wolves complete Agbadou signing|website=wolves.co.uk|date=9 January 2025|accessdate=9 January 2025}}</ref>

Agbadou scored his first goal for Wolves in their match against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] on 20 May 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.livescore.com/en/football/england/premier-league/crystal-palace-vs-wolves/1250935/|title=Crystal Palace vs Wolverhampton Wanderers – 20 May 2025|website=Livescore.com|date=20 May 2025|accessdate=20 May 2025}}</ref>

On 1 November 2025, Agbadou was shown a straight red card for fouling [[Joshua King (footballer, born 2007)|Josh King]] in their 3–0 defeat to [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] and what proved to be [[Vítor Pereira (footballer, born 1968)|Vítor Pereira]]'s last game in charge as the next day he was sacked after his team went 10 games without a win in the new season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c30v7e5vvdrt|website=BBC Sport|title=Fulham 3–0 Wolverhampton Wanderers|date=1 November 2025|accessdate=3 November 2025}}</ref>

===Beşiktaş===
On 6 February 2026, Agbadou joined [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]] on a four-and-a-half-year deal for a reported fee of €18 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20260206-agbadou-completes-besiktas-move/|title=Agbadou completes Besiktas move|publisher=[[Wolves.co.uk]]|date=6 February 2026|access-date=6 February 2026|language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
Agbadou debuted with the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]] in a friendly 3–0 loss to [[England national football team|England]] on 29 March 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/34230/England_Ivory_Coast.html|title=England vs. Ivory Coast|first=Benjamin|last=Strack-Zimmermann|website=national-football-teams.com}}</ref>

On 8 October 2021, Agbadou earned his first cap for the Ivory Coast national team in a match against [[Malawi national football team|Malawi]]. He came on as a substitute for [[Serge Aurier]] in a game that his team won 3–0.

Agbadou was included in the list of Ivorian players selected by coach [[Emerse Faé]] to participate in the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=Nicolas Pépé et Simon Adingra absents, Wilfried Zaha de retour : la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la CAN |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Nicolas-pepe-et-simon-adingra-absents-wilfried-zaha-de-retour-la-liste-de-la-cote-d-ivoire-pour-la-can/1615689 |website=www.lequipe.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=CAN 2025: la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire, tenante du titre, avec le retour de Wilfried Zaha |url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20251209-can-2025-la-liste-de-la-c%C3%B4te-d-ivoire-tenante-du-titre-avec-le-retour-de-wilfried-zaha |website=www.rfi.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On May 15, 2026, Agbadou was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Faé]] in his list of 26 players in order to participate in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

